@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'HaffaChainy' where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 8
colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any chainlink you desire, this will rotate it by 90
degrees. If a neighbouring link is compatible and of the same colour,
both chainlinks will connect together. You can always rotate a chainlink
even if it is already connected to another one.

  When a chain of 3 or more chainlinks is completed, it is removed from
the board and the chainlinks on the upper rows will fall in the emptied
spaces. If the fallen chainlinks create chains of 3 chainlinks or more,
these will also be removed and you'll get points accordingly.

  A chain with 3 chainlinks will give you 1 point, but if you create
a chain using 4 chainlinks you will get 10 points, or more as each
additional chainlink over 3 multiply the number of points by 10.

  As you progress in the game, some of the following tiles will appear
from time to time:

  -Bombs:             A bomb tile (indicated by an 'electric flash'-like
                      icon) when clicked on, it will explode and eliminate
                      the chainlinks that are around it.
  -Frozen chainlinks: These chainlinks are indicated by white 'ice cubes',
                      they cannot be rotated. But they can be linked to
                      compatible chainlinks.
  -Blocks:            These always appear from the lowest rows and only
                      when a space there is emptied, if a space immediately
                      over it is emptied, another block will appear there
                      and so on, up to the uppermost row.
  -Siamese tiles:     These tiles are represented by a 4-sided star with
                      a dot in the center. If a siamese tile is located
                      next to another, both will be eliminated.

  The game ends when it is not possible to make chains of at least 3 links.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

  3 buttons are shown in the game window:

 -Minimize game window: This button indicated by a small triangle icon,
                        is located on the lower left of the window. It
                        minimizes the size of the game window while 
                        keeping the same gameboard tile size.
 -About:                Displays the informations about the game.
 -Top 10:               Displays the current best scores, the scores
                        are saved in a file called "Haff_Links", that
                        is loaded when the game is started. If that
                        file is not present, the game creates a
                        default Top 10.

 Also there's a pull-down menu containing the following items:

 -About:        Displays the informations about the game.
 -Reset Top 10: Deletes the current Top 10 file if it is present,
                and resets all the Top 10 scores to zero. 
 -Quit:         Quits the game (you can also use the
                Right-Amiga + "Q" keyboard equivalent).

